    "body": "### Problem\n\nseems `vim.api.nvim_buf_set_extmark` is based on window default\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n![Screenshot from 2023-09-17 22-39-53](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/97107165/2978d60d-c12c-4a5b-85a3-7fc28fcd4a6f)\r\n:so<CR>\r\n![Screenshot from 2023-09-17 22-41-12](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/97107165/34bd9c2f-3b30-4b5b-b914-db59aa78bd36)\r\nmove the cursor to line-end\r\n![Screenshot from 2023-09-17 22-41-57](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/assets/97107165/1c2a671b-8480-4d57-a703-2196cfc9cfb8)\r\nas you can see, the `virt text` is moving while the cursor moving to the end.\r\n\r\n`virt text` should be based on buffer. not window(as you can see, i didn't set the virt_text_win_col)          \r\n â€¢ virt_text_win_col : position the virtual text at a fixed\r\n                    window column (starting from the first text column of the\r\n                    screen line) instead of \"virt_text_pos\".\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nvirt text not moving\n\n### Neovim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.10.0-dev-1134+g677df72e4 Build type: Release LuaJIT 2.1.1694940244 Run \"nvim -V1 -v\" for more info\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nguess no.\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nLinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nKitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm256\n\n### Installation\n\nCompiled manually",
